race.description: Road To Magic Millions Qtis 3YO Maiden Plate
race.comment: Plenty of win chances.  BON VADER (1) was well supported on debut and came home hard to finish third. Fitter again and can only be improved by the experience. NOTTINGTON PRINCE (4) ran a much improved race second-up at Ipswich beaten in a photo. Drawn well and should be winding into the finish again. ON POINT PIXIE (8) has been ticking along well and rates well enough on best figures. Has placed 4/6 on rain affected ground so is a must include. SHORTCUT (11) turned in a fair effort last start when resuming, beaten 3 lengths into third over 1200m at this track. Has handled slow ground and is likely to be fitter for the fresh-up run.
